spanishExample: Consigue lo que quiere usando esto.
englishTranslation: He gets what he wants using this.

spanishExample: Siempre le pago a un detective porque no soy estúpida.
englishTranslation: I always pay a detective because I’m not stupid(f).

spanishExample: El sargento es muy divertido e interesante y eso es raro para un sargento.
englishTranslation: The sergeant is really fun and interesting and that’s weird for a sergeant.

spanishExample: ¡Consigue un taxi y págalo!
englishTranslation: Get a taxi and pay for it!

spanishExample: ¡Dámela! Es maravillosa.
englishTranslation: Give it(f) to me! It’s wonderful.

spanishExample: El avión no funciona, así que no hay un vuelo hoy.
englishTranslation: The plane doesn’t work, so there isn’t a flight today.

spanishExample: El capitán quiere ganar la carrera.
englishTranslation: The captain wants to win the race.

spanishExample: Este es el que uso y mi primo lo quiere, ¡dáselo!
englishTranslation: This one(m) is the one I use and my cousin wants it; give it to him!

spanishExample: Conseguí lo imposible y tenía que decírtelo.
englishTranslation: I got the impossible and I had to tell it to you.

spanishExample: El carro no funciona, díselo.
englishTranslation: The car doesn’t work, tell it to him.

spanishExample: Usa esta en vez de esa, esa es terrible.
englishTranslation: Use this one(f) instead of that one(f), that one(f) is terrible.

spanishExample: No había tráfico y fue maravilloso.
englishTranslation: There wasn’t any traffic and it was wonderful.

spanishExample: Te usan y eso es terrible.
englishTranslation: They use you and that’s terrible.

spanishExample: ¡Bienvenido! Estas vacaciones van a ser divertidas.
englishTranslation: Welcome! This vacation is going to be fun.

spanishExample: Creí que era imposible, ¡esto es excelente!
englishTranslation: I thought it was impossible, this is excellent!

spanishExample: Si sabe qué pasó, dígamelo, por favor.
englishTranslation: (Formal) If you know what happened, tell me it, please.

spanishExample: Mi papel es saberlo todo, así que tienes que decírmelo.
englishTranslation: My role is to know it all, so you have to tell it to me.

spanishExample: Si ella gana, dímelo.
englishTranslation: If she wins, tell me it.

spanishExample: Ganó algo raro.
englishTranslation: He won something weird.

spanishExample: ¡Dámelo! Parece interesante.
englishTranslation: Give it to me! It seems interesting.

spanishExample: Tu plan no va a funcionar, tienes que decírnoslo.
englishTranslation: Your plan isn’t going to work, you have to tell us it.

spanishExample: El soldado no es estúpido, así que tienes que dárselo.
englishTranslation: The soldier isn’t stupid, so you have to give it to him.

spanishExample: Siempre consigo lo que quiero sin decírselo.
englishTranslation: I always get what I want without telling it to her.

spanishExample: Nunca usa esa cosa.
englishTranslation: She never uses that thing.

spanishExample: ¡Bienvenida! ¿Dónde conseguiste eso?
englishTranslation: Welcome(f)! Where did you get that?

spanishExample: No he usado esto en un tiempo, tengo que usarlo.
englishTranslation: I haven’t used this in a while, I have to use it.

spanishExample: Esta comida es excelente.
englishTranslation: This food is excellent.
